wikipedia_page.main: Henry "Harry" Huth (14 February 1856 — 31 December 1929(1929-12-31) (aged 73)) born in Huddersfield, was an English cricketer and rugby union footballer who played in the 1870s. He played representative level rugby union (RU) for England, and at club level for Huddersfield, as a Fullback, i.e. number 15, he died in Kensington. Prior to Tuesday 27 August 1895, Huddersfield was a rugby union club.
